skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.1: The Bridging mod allows you to place blocks out in front of you instead of using sneak!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.10: Colors can be discovered in a variety of ways, not just crafting!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.11: Creatures don't spawn naturally. You will have to discover and unlock them individually
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.12: Crops will display an exclamation point above when fully grown!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.13: Want to prevent spawning in specific areas? You can use Mega Torches!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.14: Skeletons, Zombies, and Cats will dance next to a Jukebox playing music!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.15: Charge up your item throw distance by holding down the throw button!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.4: Many blocks and mobs can be dyed. Try clicking on them with a dye and see what happens!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.5: Looking for a delicious dipping sauce for your chicken or french fries? Make some Raising Cane's sauce! Mix Mayonnaise and Ketchup together. Add in Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, pepper, and liquid smoke for a mouthwatering experience you'll never forget!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.6: What starts with a W, and has 3 letters, but ends with a T
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.7: Sniffers are actually useful! They can dig up helpful items!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.8: Not sure what to do next? Advancements or the Task Book can help guide you!
skyfactory_5.tipsmod.tip.9: Villager's trades will periodically change. If you don't see something you like, just wait longer!
